    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To specify table borders in CSS, use the border property."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The example below specifies a solid border for <table>, <th>, and <td> elements:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table, th, td {\n  border: 1px solid;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Full-Width Table"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The table above might seem small in some cases. If you need a table that should span the entire screen (full-width), add width: 100% to the \n<table> element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table {\n    width: 100%;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Double Borders\nNotice that the table in the examples above have double borders. This is \nbecause both the table and the <th> and <td> elements have separate borders.\nTo remove double borders, take a look at the example below."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Collapse Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The border-collapse property sets whether the table borders \nshould be collapsed into a single border:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table\n{\n  border-collapse: collapse;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you only want a border around the table, only specify the border property for \n<table>:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table\n{  border: 1px solid;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
